# **API For Registering User (Company/Professional)**

API to register both the professional user and the company user.

Api will return the jwtToken which should be stored for authorization later

Note: The jwtToken that is return from the api should be used later to call API's that requires authentication by adding it in the authorization header (Bearer Token)

## Request Type: multipart form-data

Request Format

#### **Professional User**

| Field Name | required | type | description | example |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| userType | true | text | The user type, for professional user value must be professional | professional |
| firstName | true | text | First name of the user |  |
| lastName | false | text | Last name of the user |  |
| email | true | text | Email of the user |  |
| password | true | text | Password of the user |  |
| phoneNumber | false | text | Phone number of the user |  |
| description | false | text | Brief Description of the User |  |
| dob | true | text | Date of birth of the user in YYYY-MM-dd format | 2000-01-30 |
| socialURL | false | text | LinkedinUrl of the Professional user |  |
| address | false | text | address of the user |  |
| tags | false | text | Tags that the user choose which is a tag string followed up with comas and then the other tag string | tag1,tag2,tag3 |
| userimage | false | file | The user image, Must be either jpg or png |  |

#### **Company User**

| Field Name | required | type | description | example |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| userType | true | text | The user type, for professional user value must be professional | professional |
| firstName | true | text | First name of the user |  |
| lastName | false | text | Second name of the Company |  |
| email | true | text | Email of the user |  |
| password | true | text | Password of the user |  |
| description | false | text | Brief Description of company |  |
| phoneNumber | false | text | Phone number of the user |  |
| abn | true | text | ABN of the company. 11 digits (can be with space or not with space) | 51 824 753 556 |
| socialURL | false | text | Company Website URL or company social media url |  |
| address | false | text | address of the user |  |
| tags | false | text | Tags that the user choose which is a tag string followed up with comas and then the other tag string | tag1,tag2,tag3 |
| userimage | false | file | The user image, Must be either jpg or png |  |

## Response Type: json

Response for both Professional user and company user

| Field Name | type | description | example |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| name | text | User name of the user | John Doe |
| email | text | Email of the user |  |
| jwtToken | text | jwt of the user | JWT {token here} |

# **API For Editting a User (Company/Professional/Admin)**

## **IMPORTANT: THIS API REQUIRES THE JWT TOKEN IN THE AUTHORIZATION HEADER**

API to edit a user profile

So this API has 2 types of mode:

- Request with no userId: When there is no userId inserted, the api will update the profile of the user associated with the authentication token
- Request with userId: API will update the profile of the user specified in the userID but keep in mind that only users with admin authentication level can update another users profile. If a professional/company user call this API to update another user profile then the API will return an error
    

## Request Type: multipart form-data

Request Format

#### **Professional User**

request.description:
# **API For Paginating Users (Company/Professional)**

API to paginate users by userType and also their tags

## Request Type: json

Request Format

|  | required | type | description | example |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| userType | true | text | The user type, either professional or company | professional |
| size | true | number | The size of the pagination you want to get | 4 |
| page | true | number | The page of the pagination you want to fetch (Starts from 1) | 1 |
| tags | false | Array | Array of text that represents the tags you want to use as a filter | \[tag1,tag2\] |
| sort | false | rating asc|desc | To sort the result by the rating | rating asc |

## Response Type: json

Response for both Professional user and company user

| Field Name | type | description | example |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| userList | Array | An Array of Documents representing the users. Further information about the user type data type can be seen on the table below | Can see from the examples |
| amountOfUser | number | Number of total users based on the filter given in the api |  |
| size | number | the size of each pagination page |  |
| totalPages | number | The total number of pages available based on the pagination filters that is provided |  |
| currentPage | number | The current page number in the pagination |  |
| hasPrevPage | boolean | Just ignore this one |  |
| hasNextPage | boolean | Just ignore this one |  |
| prevPage | number | null | The number of the previous page of this pagination result. Will be null if there is no prevPage |
| nextPage | number | null | The number of the next page of this pagination result, will be null if there is no nextPage |
|  |  |  |  |
